The above heuristics are possible because there are specific words and/or phrases in dictionary definitions, forming what we shall call here patterns, which are almost systematically used to express specific semantic relations (Markowitz et al.1986). For the two relations considered here, some of these patterns are: INSTRUMENT: for, used for, used to, a means for, etc.
